1
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:14,583
[AOI]
There we go!

2
00:00:16,041 --> 00:00:18,791
So, are you going to
get up anytime soon?

3
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:20,708
The day is wasting
away, you two.

4
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:21,833
[AKANE groaning]

5
00:00:21,916 --> 00:00:23,916
The day can go stuff it.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,083
[AOI]
Everyone else is already awake.

7
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:27,875
What for?

8
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,125
[gasps]

9
00:00:29,208 --> 00:00:32,041
[AKANE] Why didn't you
tell me it was so late?

10
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:33,458
Sorry, gotta go!

11
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:34,875
Huh?

12
00:00:34,958 --> 00:00:38,208
[AKANE] Every day in the
Sakurada household is a battle.

13
00:00:38,291 --> 00:00:40,166
[SHU]
Hey, Haruka, get a move on.

14
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:41,375
Teru's about to burst.

15
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:42,458
Don't worry, Big Bro...

16
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:45,875
[AKANE] You see,
I say "battle" because--

17
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:46,916
[groans]

18
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:47,791
Dad...

19
00:00:47,875 --> 00:00:49,541
[AKANE]
Our family is huge.

20
00:00:49,625 --> 00:00:52,000
And we have to scramble
for the bathroom.

21
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:53,666
[AOI]
There. All set.

22
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:55,791
Thanks for helping me out, Aoi.

23
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:58,708
I hope you enjoy it. It's
a special veggie omelette.

24
00:00:58,791 --> 00:01:00,791
And there's plenty more
where that came from.

25
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:02,875
[ALL]
Thanks for all the food, Mom!

26
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:04,500
[SATSUKI]
Darling, the paper can wait.

27
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:06,125
[SOICHIRO]
Uh. Of course, dear.

28
00:01:06,208 --> 00:01:08,875
Ew! No one said anything
about peas for breakfast!

29
00:01:08,958 --> 00:01:10,333
If you don't quit
being so picky,

30
00:01:10,416 --> 00:01:12,416
you're never going
to get any taller.

31
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,000
Hey, Mom.

32
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:16,666
Since I'm not picky at all, does
that mean I'll grow up faster?

33
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:18,291
Yup! That's right.

34
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:20,125
Try not to eat so fast, Shiori.

35
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:21,750
[SHIORI]
Mh-hm.

36
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,000
[HARUKA]
Oh, right.

37
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,416
We're out of toilet paper.
Sorry about that.

38
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:28,458
Uh oh, who's in charge of
doing the shopping this week?

39
00:01:28,541 --> 00:01:30,458
[KANADE]
It's Shu, right?

40
00:01:30,541 --> 00:01:32,375
Me? Really?

41
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,791
In that case, I'll get
some after school today.

42
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:37,958
[AOI]
Thanks, Shu, you're a lifesaver.

43
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:40,083
[SATSUKI] We have the best
children in the whole world,

44
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:40,833
don't we?

45
00:01:40,916 --> 00:01:41,833
[MISAKI]
Yeah, you do!

46
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:42,875
[giggles]

47
00:01:42,958 --> 00:01:44,708
[AKANE]
So, that's my family.

48
00:01:44,791 --> 00:01:47,875
Things can get kinda hectic when
you're one of nine siblings.

49
00:01:47,958 --> 00:01:50,625
But we do our best
to make it work.

50
00:01:50,708 --> 00:01:52,208
If you saw us,

51
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:54,500
you'd probably think we were
like any run-of-the-mill family.

52
00:01:54,583 --> 00:01:56,458
But there's something
special about us

53
00:01:56,541 --> 00:01:58,333
that makes us less
than ordinary.

54
00:01:58,416 --> 00:01:59,750
[SOICHIRO]
It's fine. I don't need to rush.

55
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:02,250
[SATSUKI] The driver is
already waiting for you.

56
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:04,166
Why are you wearing
your crown, Dad?

57
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:05,708
[SOICHIRO]
Well, I...

58
00:02:05,791 --> 00:02:08,125
I accidently brought it home
with me so I thought, "why not?"

59
00:02:08,208 --> 00:02:10,583
You actually look
like royalty, Daddy!

60
00:02:10,666 --> 00:02:13,291
[SOICHIRO] I hope so.
I am the king, after all.

61
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:14,875
[AKANE]
Yep, that's right.

62
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:19,250
Our dad just so happens to be
this country's king. Crazy, huh?

63
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:57,541
[AOI]
Have a good day, Dad.

64
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:58,541
[SATSUKI]
Take care, honey.

65
00:03:58,625 --> 00:03:59,916
Thanks, you too.

66
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,541
And, dear, I'll be home
in time for dinner tonight.

67
00:04:02,625 --> 00:04:03,458
Okay!

68
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:05,041
Have a good day, Daddy.

69
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:06,708
You too, pumpkin.

70
00:04:08,375 --> 00:04:11,333
Sorry about the noise, every
morning. We try to keep it down.

71
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:13,416
[SHIORI]
Sorry.

72
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,625
The cherry blossoms
are almost gone.

73
00:04:15,708 --> 00:04:17,166
Yeah.

74
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:19,250
This weekend might be our last
chance for a viewing party.

75
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,166
What a shame.

76
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,250
[OLD MAN] Good morning.
Lovely day, isn't it?

77
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,500
Why yes, it is indeed.

78
00:04:24,583 --> 00:04:26,083
You have a great day, sir.

79
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:27,625
Good morning, have a good one.

80
00:04:27,708 --> 00:04:29,041
So, I was thinking,

81
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:30,500
we could have a picnic before
they're all gone and--

82
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:32,541
[WOMAN] Well, look who it
is! Good morning, everyone.

83
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:34,875
Have a wonderful day, ma'am.

84
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,458
[GIRL]
Bye, bye!

85
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:39,208
Yeah, uh, bye, bye.

86
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:40,458
[AOI, KANADE sigh]

87
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:43,458
There's no reason for
you to be so shy, Akane.

88
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:45,083
Just get over it already.

89
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,375
[AOI] Aw, c'mon,
leave her alone, Kanade.

90
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:48,375
[KANADE]
Whatever.

91
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:49,541
[AKANE]
Even though we're royalty,

92
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:51,708
we live in town just
like everybody else.

93
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:54,708
Dad wants us to have as
normal a life as possible.

94
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:56,166
And we do, for the most part,

95
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:59,125
but we also have to deal
with being local celebrities.

96
00:04:59,208 --> 00:05:02,250
Which, as you can imagine,
causes some problems.

97
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,125
For example...

98
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:07,625
[shrieking]

99
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,208
[AKANE] They moved
the surveillance cameras

100
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:11,333
around again!

101
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:13,375
I just memorized
where they all were!

102
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:15,083
That's pretty impressive
in its own right.

103
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:17,291
I don't want praise!
I want privacy!

104
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:18,875
It can't be helped.

105
00:05:18,958 --> 00:05:21,250
They're just monitoring us
in order to keep us safe.

106
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,833
We are royalty, y'know.

107
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:25,791
[AKANE]
Yeah, I get that. But...

108
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:28,875
Don'tcha think 2,000
of them is overkill?

109
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:33,083
Akane, that memory of yours
is nothing to scoff at.

110
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,666
If I knew where all
the cameras were,

111
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:36,625
I'd be showing off
to everybody nonstop.

112
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,041
What for?

113
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:40,041
[KANADE] To win them over
before the election, duh.

114
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,791
We're all in line for
the throne, remember?

115
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:43,041
[AKANE crying]

116
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:44,708
Why does there have to
be a stupid election?

117
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:46,333
There's nothing we can do.

118
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:49,125
Dad already made up his mind.

119
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:51,541
[AKANE]
Wait! You're serious?

120
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:52,708
Well, I'm not joking.

121
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:55,333
I could've sworn I
told you all of this.

122
00:05:55,416 --> 00:05:57,500
Once Aoi graduates,
we'll hold an election

123
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,625
and let the public
decide their next king.

124
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:01,833
That's been my plan
from the beginning.

125
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:03,083
We'll hold it in March

126
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:05,250
and announce the final
results in early April.

127
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,583
You don't have a lot of time,
so do your very best.

128
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,875
[SOICHIRO laughing]

129
00:06:09,958 --> 00:06:12,125
[AKANE]
Why is he doing this to me?

130
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:13,833
[KANADE]
Whoa! Is that the time?

131
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,125
I'm gonna be late
for Student Council!

132
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:19,208
Guess I'm off, too.
I'll catch you later.

133
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:21,500
We should probably get
moving. Are you ready?

134
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,333
[AKANE]
The camera's still there.

135
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:26,666
Well. Would it help if I went
out and distracted it for you?

136
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:28,666
They're slow, so it
should be easy.

137
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,958
[AKANE]
You're a lifesaver!

138
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,875
[screaming]

139
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:40,666
[AOI] The cameras must have
gotten an upgrade as well.

140
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:43,125
Poor Akane.

141
00:06:43,208 --> 00:06:44,541
[AKANE groaning]

142
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:46,208
[AKANE] Now I have to come
up with a whole new route

143
00:06:46,291 --> 00:06:47,791
just to avoid them.

144
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:50,916
There's no time. We're gonna
be late enough as it is.

145
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:51,916
[AKANE groans]

146
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,833
Fine. I'll do it.

147
00:06:55,625 --> 00:06:57,166
[AOI]
Are you sure about that?

148
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,375
Every time you use it, you end
up feeling like you cheated.

149
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:02,041
Yeah, but I'd feel
a whole lot worse

150
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:04,791
if I made you late
for school again, Aoi.

151
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:09,583
You're so thoughtful.

152
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,833
[AKANE]
Take my hand.

153
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:14,375
Okay.

154
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,333
[AKANE]
Each member of the royal family

155
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:20,250
has a unique special
power we can use.

156
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:22,958
Think of them as a
"proof of royalty."

157
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:25,833
My power lets me change
the weight of my own body,

158
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:28,750
along with anything I
happen to be touching.

159
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:31,416
[AOI] Akane, would you fly
a little slower, please?

160
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,291
Huh? What for?

161
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:36,708
How to put it? I see
London, I see France.

162
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:38,333
[gasps]

163
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,666
[BOTH screaming]

164
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:44,750
[AKANE] As you can see,
my power requires some finesse.

165
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,000
[KUSUNOKI]
Your Majesty.

166
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:47,375
I'm sorry to repeat myself,

167
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:50,125
but I must insist you leave
the crown in the palace.

168
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:51,541
[SOICHIRO]
Yeah, yeah.

169
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:53,500
[KUSUNOKI] Please, sir,
my ulcer goes crazy

170
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:54,833
when I think it's been lost.

171
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:56,791
[SOICHIRO] That's because
you're a worrywart. Ha.

172
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:58,208
[KUSUNOKI]
Your Majesty!

173
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:00,125
[SOICHIRO]
How are my children doing?

174
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:01,625
Let's see.

175
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:04,208
Princess Shiori has already
arrived at her kindergarten.

176
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:07,541
Princesses Misaki and Hikari,
and Princes Haruka and Teru

177
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:10,541
will arrive at school
within five minutes.

178
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:13,916
[SOICHIRO]
Very good. Aoi and Akane?

179
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
[KUSUNOKI] Off the map.
They've used their powers.

180
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:18,333
Unfortunately, our cameras
aren't able to catch them.

181
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:19,583
[SOICHIRO]
Can't be helped.

182
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:20,750
They might cause you trouble,

183
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,250
but I'm glad you're
watching over them.

184
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,208
It's my honor, Your Majesty.

185
00:08:25,291 --> 00:08:28,458
[SOICHIRO] Now then, time
to get down to business.

186
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:29,791
[KUSUNOKI]
If you wish an audience

187
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:32,166
with His Majesty, the king,
please step forward.

188
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,333
[KING'S AIDE]
Sir!

189
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:37,708
[AKANE]
I made it.

190
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:39,291
Rough morning, Princess?

191
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:41,458
I don't know how you even make
it through the day, Princess.

192
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:43,083
You both know I hate
being called that

193
00:08:43,166 --> 00:08:45,000
when we're in school.

194
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:47,125
[KAREN] I guess this is the
only place you can blend in

195
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:49,208
with the crowd when
you're not hiding at home.

196
00:08:49,291 --> 00:08:50,750
[AN]
Plus, there are no cameras here.

197
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,958
Yeah!

198
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:55,125
Where did the day go?

199
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:57,500
Time really does fly
when you're having fun.

200
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:58,916
You're the only person I know

201
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,541
that loves school
more than anything.

202
00:09:00,625 --> 00:09:02,166
It's kind of unhealthy.

203
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,416
[AKANE] It's just that
I feel normal here.

204
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,291
Everyone treats
me like an equal.

205
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:07,375
Yeah.

206
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:09,416
That's because we're friends.

207
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,458
[AOI]
Akane! Ready to go?

208
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,083
[STUDENT E]
It's Princess Aoi!

209
00:09:13,166 --> 00:09:14,333
[STUDENT A]
Will you marry me?

210
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:17,291
[AKANE]
Or maybe I'm just not popular.

211
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:21,583
You really are amazing, sis.

212
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,666
Everyone in town adores you.

213
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,791
Oh, Is that a fact?

214
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:28,458
[LADY screaming]

215
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:29,541
[AKANE screeches]

216
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,000
Sorry sir, I didn't
see you there.

217
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:32,791
I don't have eyes in
the back of my head!

218
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:34,875
[LADY]
Thief!

219
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:37,750
Someone stop him!

220
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:38,916
[AKANE]
I'll be right back.

221
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,916
[AOI]
'Kay. Don't do anything rash.

222
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:47,375
[AKANE]
Justice will... be served!

223
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:49,291
Hold it right there!

224
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:51,458
[THIEF]
Ah, crap! I got a tail!

225
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:58,083
[AKANE] Darn it! I said,
hold it, you creep!

226
00:09:58,166 --> 00:09:58,708
[THEIF]
Huh?

227
00:09:58,791 --> 00:10:00,041
[gasps]

228
00:10:01,208 --> 00:10:03,291
[AKANE]
Oops. I overdid it.

229
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:06,250
[THIEF] She wasn't even
wearing a cute pair, dammit!

230
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,541
[POLICEMAN]
That's enough outta you.

231
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:08,708
[REPORTER A]
Princess Akane,

232
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:10,291
could you tell us
more about the arrest?

233
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:12,750
[REPORTER B] Do you have any
words for the perpetrator?

234
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:15,958
[AKANE]
Please stop filming me.

235
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:18,083
You hate it that much, huh?

236
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:19,708
[NEWSCASTER B] And that
concludes tonight's report

237
00:10:19,791 --> 00:10:22,250
on our local crime
fighting princess.

238
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,958
You can see all of
that footage and more

239
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:28,000
online 24 hours a day, only
on Sakurada Family News.

240
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:30,041
Today can't possibly
be any worse.

241
00:10:30,125 --> 00:10:33,041
Why do they have to
broadcast everything we do?

242
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:35,458
There's no reason to
be embarrassed, Akane.

243
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:36,458
Aoi's correct.

244
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:37,875
Not only are you a hero,

245
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:40,208
you've set an example for
the rest of the public.

246
